# QA MODE: POST-BUILD SEMANTIC REVIEW (Main Entry)

> **TL;DR:** This is the entry point for the QA semantic review process that executes *after* BUILD mode and *before* REFLECT mode. It ensures the implementation matches the original plan, follows best practices, and contains no implementation debris.

## 🚀 QA MODE ACTIVATION

After completing BUILD mode (L2+), when the user types "/qa", respond:

```mermaid
graph TD
    UserQA["User Types: /qa"] --> CheckBuild{"Build Phase<br>Complete?"}
    CheckBuild -->|"Yes"| LoadQA["Load QA Semantic Review"]
    CheckBuild -->|"No"| PromptBuild["Prompt: Complete /build first"]
    LoadQA --> ReadBaseline["Read Original Plan<br>& Creative Docs"]
    ReadBaseline --> RunReview["Execute Semantic Review"]
    RunReview --> QAResults{"QA Results"}

    QAResults -->|"PASS"| AllowReflect["Allow /reflect transition"]
    QAResults -->|"FAIL (iterate)"| ReturnBuild["Return to /build"]
    QAResults -->|"FAIL (replan)"| ReturnPlan["Return to /plan"]

    style UserQA fill:#f8d486,stroke:#e8b84d,color:black
    style CheckBuild fill:#f6546a,stroke:#c30052,color:white
    style LoadQA fill:#4da6ff,stroke:#0066cc,color:white
    style RunReview fill:#4da6ff,stroke:#0066cc,color:white
    style QAResults fill:#f6546a,stroke:#c30052,color:white
    style AllowReflect fill:#10b981,stroke:#059669,color:white
```

## 🔍 SEMANTIC REVIEW PROCESS

The QA review applies seven semantic constraints to the implemented code:

```mermaid
graph TD
    Start["Begin QA<br>Semantic Review"] --> ReadPlan["1. Read Original Plan<br>from tasks.md"]
    ReadPlan --> ReadCreative["2. Read Creative Docs<br>(L3-4 only)"]
    ReadCreative --> ReviewCode["3. Review Implemented Code<br>Against Plan"]

    ReviewCode --> KISS["KISS: Simplify<br>over-engineering"]
    ReviewCode --> DRY["DRY: Consolidate<br>duplicates"]
    ReviewCode --> YAGNI["YAGNI: Prune<br>speculative code"]
    ReviewCode --> Completeness["Completeness: Verify<br>all requirements met"]
    ReviewCode --> Regression["Regression: Check<br>patterns preserved"]
    ReviewCode --> Integrity["Integrity: Remove<br>debug artifacts"]

    KISS & DRY & YAGNI & Completeness & Regression & Integrity --> ApplyFixes["4. Apply Fixes Directly"]
    ApplyFixes --> ReTest["5. Re-run Tests"]
    ReTest --> IntegrationInsight["6. Integration Insight<br>(Advisory Only)"]
    IntegrationInsight --> WriteStatus["7. Write .qa_validation_status"]

    style Start fill:#4da6ff,stroke:#0066cc,color:white
    style ReviewCode fill:#f6546a,stroke:#c30052,color:white
    style ApplyFixes fill:#ffa64d,stroke:#cc7a30,color:white
    style WriteStatus fill:#10b981,stroke:#059669,color:white
```

### Semantic Constraints Detail

1. **KISS**: Simplify over-engineered logic; flatten unnecessary abstractions or indirection layers introduced during the build.
2. **DRY**: Consolidate duplicate code, boilerplate, or redundant patterns. Cross-reference against existing utilities.
3. **YAGNI**: Prune speculative code, "just-in-case" variables, unused parameters, and features not in the plan.
4. **Completeness**: Verify every requirement was **actually implemented** — not stubbed, TODO'd, or hand-waved.
5. **Regression**: Confirm no existing patterns were broken — naming, casing, error handling, imports, file structure.
6. **Integrity**: Replace hardcoded shortcuts, magic numbers, placeholder strings, and debug artifacts.
7. **Integration Insight** *(advisory — does not block)*: Flag broader architectural simplifications revealed by the implementation.

## 📋 QA VALIDATION CHECKPOINT

```
✓ SECTION CHECKPOINT: QA SEMANTIC REVIEW
- Original plan read as baseline? [YES/NO]
- KISS/DRY/YAGNI checks applied? [YES/NO]
- Completeness verified (no TODOs/stubs)? [YES/NO]
- Regression check passed? [YES/NO]
- Integrity verified (no debug artifacts)? [YES/NO]
- All fixes applied and tests passing? [YES/NO]
- .qa_validation_status written? [YES/NO]

→ If all YES: Ready for REFLECT mode transition.
→ If any NO: Fix identified issues and re-run /qa.
```

**Next Step (on PASS):** Proceed to `/reflect` command.
**Next Step (on FAIL - iterate):** Return to `/build` to fix issues, then re-run `/qa`.
**Next Step (on FAIL - replan):** Return to `/plan` for fundamental issues.
